        <exercise xml:id="workshop-exponents-summary-of-properties-materials">
          <title>Applying the properties of exponents</title>
        <statement>
          <p>
            Follow this link to find a summary of the properties of exponents: <xref ref ="workshop-exponents-summary-of-properties">Written Examples</xref>
          </p>
          <p>
            Completely simplify each expression.  Your final expression should contain no negative exponents.  Assume that all variables represent positive numbers.
            <ol cols="3">
              <li><m>x^8 \cdot x^{21}</m></li>
              <li><m>(x^7)^{10}</m></li>
              <li><m>\frac{x^{17}}{x^{11}}</m></li>
              <li><m>\frac{x^{14}}{x^{23}}</m></li>
              <li><m>2x^{-31}</m></li>
              <li><m>\frac{1}{x^{-96}}</m></li>
              <li><m>-x^{-2}</m></li>
              <li><m>(x^4y^{-3})^5</m></li>
              <li><m>\frac{x^4x^{-6}}{5x^{-2}}</m></li>
              <li><m>\left(\frac{4x^{-7}}{y^{-2}}\right)^{-6}</m></li>
              <li><m>\left(\frac{4x^{-1}y^{12}z^{-3}}{(x^2y^{-3}\right)^{-6}})^0</m></li>
              <li><m>\frac{(xy^{-4})^{-2}}{(3x^{-1})^2}</m></li>
            </ol>
          </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <p>
            <ol>
              <li><m>x^8 \cdot x^{21}=x^{29}</m></li>
              <li><m>(x^7)^{10}=x^{70}</m></li>
